metadata.name: Patches #239
metadata.description:
This token generates a colorful abstract artwork that appears as watercolor on fabric. Project began as exploration of palettes used in famous masterpieces listed on Color Lisa web site. 97 color combinations used by great artists are applied here on abstract art.

Each piece is generated by bio inspired cellular automata in which colors from chosen palette are competing for domination on canvas. There are three different configurations of space fragmentation and each one is producing specific style.

metadata.name: MOYO #100
metadata.description:
MOYO is generative piece building unique patterns.
The first algorithm was created in 2018, while visiting Kanazawa, a city on the west side of Japan.
Originally inspired by some kimono embroidery, I created some set of rules that will give life, recursively, to patterns generated inside a squared area.

Thanks to fxhash, I can pursue the original generative vision of those patterns by evolving the algorithm, and here comes MOYO.
This collection of 1024 pieces waiting to be minted offers new compositions, new rules and new colors.
During the iterative crafting process, I've been surprised by the algorithm which offered some unexpected kind of results, which have been kept for the final generation.

Artist: Florian Zumbrunn
@florianzumbrunn

metadata.name: Distant Views #42
metadata.description:
This work explores generative way of painting landscapes on canvas. Algorithm uses backward moves with big polygon brush to produce mountain-like structures. Shades of randomly selected color make illusion of distance and adds to diversity of terrain. Sun and Moon can have different positions on the horizon or not be visible at all. Their color changes depending on the position. Besides night and day, there are three rough variants of composition based on percentage that sky takes on canvas. There is a also chance to have snowy mountain on top.

Artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

December, 2021.

metadata.name: éclats #202
metadata.description:
Started as a simple exploration of circle packing, this generative piece became "éclats".
I play around colors, contrasts and details to create some kind of lights. Some composition and palette might remind you some fireworks, some cities viewed from the sky, some flower fields or... Whatever comes to your mind.

Note: depending on the features, the generation might take a bit of time.

metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #568
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Kinetics #250
metadata.description:
CONTROLS
 * Pause a Kinetic by clicking on the canvas.
 * Increase and decrease the p5js framerate by tapping the left and right arrows.
 * Pause the top layer by tapping down arrow.
 * Save a frame by tapping S.
 * Press H for High Quality, M for Default, L for Low Quality. Note, this effects performance.
 * Reset the Kinetic by by tapping backspace.

Kinetics is a neo-constructivist generative art project built using p5js. Each Kinetic delicately moves from it's origin, giving the appearance of infinite space and possibility. The viewer witnesses the construction of the Kinetic floating inside of the negative. Shapes and lines move around the Kinetic in a dazzling display of contrasting color.

The texture developed for Kinetics, deemed The Creation of the Universe (See top right) is at its core a color gradient of 3 different colors. Each piece construct's itself, drawing lines on top of lines to create a unique self contained assembly of materials as opposed to a realistic abstraction. The Creation of the Universe repeats itself in each piece, just as cells do in an organic structure. From here is where it initially got it's name.

Inspired heavily by the works of Rodchenko and Tatlin, each Kinetic appears to slot together like a puzzle. Each piece has multiple hard edge planes clashing aggressively with each other giving the sense that there is more than just a flat canvas. A quasi realism is created through our desire to build instead of simply paint.

"Long Live Generative Art"

- Mitchell

metadata.name: Deep Sea Oysters #25
metadata.description:
Oysters normally dwell in undeep waters. Some however are found on several hundred meters depth. These collection of special ones are living their happy covert lives in the depths of deep sea. They're waiting for you to press mint, and one them will come to life. Beware! Sometimes lightning strikes and a convoluted one will show up.

Proudly created in P5.
Press 'f' to save.
